# Trivy vulnerability ignore file
#
# These CVEs cannot be fixed by updating project dependencies.
#
# GHSA-gv7w-rqvm-qjhr (esbuild): Affects Deno module binary integrity.
# We don't use Deno, and esbuild is a build-time-only dev dependency.
# astro/vite pin esbuild to ^0.27.3; forcing ^0.28.x breaks Astro's
# dynamic module imports. This is a build-tool CVE with no runtime risk.
#
# CVE-2026-33176 (activesupport): Ruby gem vulnerability found in
# Gemfile.lock files bundled inside the published npm package
# @stellar/js-xdr (under node_modules). These are third-party Ruby
# dependencies — we cannot update them.

# esbuild (build-time tool, Deno-specific CVE, astro/vite pin to 0.27.x)
GHSA-gv7w-rqvm-qjhr

# activesupport in @stellar/js-xdr's bundled Gemfile.lock (third-party Ruby dep)
CVE-2026-33176
